HEADWORD: Haikal
<hw>Hai"kal</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧"k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
central chapel of the three forming the sanctuary of a Coptic church. It
contains the high altar, and is usually closed by an embroidered
curtain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

